@node eng_overall "One-size overalls fit all"

The game Excavation is an arcade/strategy game set in the @{"underworld" link "eng_underworld"}. In this
game, the player is in charge of an Excavation Company and its four Excavators.
The Excavators work in a deep mine, digging up jewels so that the Company can
sell them.

This is as far as the overall node goes. Read other topics for more
information...
@endnode
@node eng_plot "Story so far"
The planet of Mineralia is a pretty nice planet.
  Its diameter is about one and a half times that of Earth, and it consists
mainly of earth and rock. Few beings live there, apart from ghosts, amoebae,
and excavation companies.

Zwok Zwok Zwok had been, in his youth, the managing director of an excavation
company, called simply The Excavation Company. But now he was growing weary.
  The Excavation Company had several buildings situated above excavatable
ground in various places around the planet. Nobody knew what lurked below the
surface, for nobody had dared enter the shafts for many decades.
  There might be monsters. Indeed, some said, there were monsters. But there
also were gems, beautiful gems that everybody wanted to buy. So the company had
to go on.

Zwok Zwok Zwok had grown so weary that he thought he wouldn't last as a
managing director any more. So he chose to abdicate.

But who would inherit the title? Since he had no children left, the heir ought
to be one of his three grandchildren.
  First he thought of Vera. But Vera was an adventurous woman now, who had
already had two husbands and was about to marry a third one. Her second husband
had given her his surname Lynn. And the person she was about to marry was
called Akko. She was thinking something along the lines of Vera Lynn-Akko.
  Then he thought of Chuck. But Chuck had got married too, to a certain mrs.
Brown. They had even bought a dog, a black-and-white beagle, as far as Zwok
could recall.
  Lastly he thought of Dave. Dave was not eligible either, because he was a
teacher now. He teached general education for three students. They all had
some kind of mental delusion.
  Christopher Alvin (known as C.Alvin or simply Alvin) thought he had a friend,
whose name was Thomas Hobbes. Simon thought he was a sorceror. And Theodore -
well, he thought he sold vacuum cleaners.

So Zwok had no relatives left. He had a brilliant idea - he threw the company
open to the public - everybody could buy franchises of it and make a fortune by
excavating for gems and then selling them, buying equipment to excavate more
gems.
  It was well. Soon everybody across the planet was buying franchises, until
Zwok had grown tired of his own people's inability to lead excavation business,
so he declared instead that the directors must be from another planet.
  Nobody came until one shuttlecraft landed from a distant planet, called
Tellus. It contained a being who soon bought a franchise and started hiring
local people as his excavators. All was well... for now!

        YOU are this being! You must successfully guide your four
        excavators and make them search for gems, use equipment and
        excavate even deeper and deeper! Good Luck!

@endnode
@node eng_menu "Today's a la Carte"

The main menu has six actions for you to perform:

    - Create a world
This (or loading a saved game) is necessary for you to access the game itself
at all. Basically what this does is create a whole new world for you, making
all those little passages and caverns, and putting the @{"objects and creatures"} link "eng_objects"}
in place.

    - Load a saved game (not available in @{"unregistered" link "eng_money"} version)
Loads a saved game from disk, surprisingly. It also checks whether the file is
really an Excavation saved game or not. If it isn't, you are left with no
world at all.

    - Delete a file from disk
Guess! This will work on any file, not just Excavation saved games.

    - Go!
Click this button to enter the mystical world of Excavation!

    - Music
Allows you to choose a music for the game. The music has to be in .abk "Music"
format, and the music bank must be #3, and it must be the only bank in the
file. Pretty impressive, innit?

    - Quit
This button is reserved for top professionals. Anybody who isn't a Computer
Guru and/or hasn't got an IQ of over 160 shouldn't touch this button at all.
Pretend it doesn't exist.

Just click on the corresponding button to do whatever you please.
@endnode
@node eng_base "Chemistry rules - but where's the Acid?"

The Base is the brain of your Excavation Company. The Base is always present,
and cannot be destroyed in any way.
  When you start the game, you will automatically enter the Base. If you are
controlling an Excavator, you can return to the Base by pressing HELP.

In the base, you can carry out all sorts of operations. Here is an overview of
them.

    - Trade
You can buy and sell loads of different things, like @{"Equipment" link "eng_equip"}, Power and
Food, and Jewels. Just click on the topmost buttons to select your "trade
page".
  The trade itself is a little more complex. To actually buy/sell something,
you must do the following:
  - If you are trading Equipment, you must first select your Equipment from
the page.
  - Find a black box with white numbers. Click on it and type the number of
things you wish to buy/sell, and press Return.
  - If there's a +/- button next to the black box, toggle it so that it reads
+ if you are going to buy stuff, or - if you will sell stuff.
  - Then click on a Buy, Sell or Buy/Sell button.

    - Outfit Excavators
There are four buttons which allow you to choose one of your Excavators for
outfitting. Here's an overview of things you can do to your Excavator:
  - You can give him @{"Equipment" link "eng_equip"}. Just select what Equipment you want to give
him (or take from him) and then click on one of his Equipment slots. The left
mouse button gives Equipment, the right one takes it away.
  - You can give him Power and Food. Just click on the black boxes and type the
new values you want.
  - You can give his Jewels to the Base. Press the little arrow buttons to
transfer all Jewels, or type the numbers on the black boxes.
  - You can eject an Excavator from the base, either on the left side or on
the right side.
  - You can hire a new Excavator. This costs 2000 money, and the Excavator has
to be dead in order to do this.

    - Maps & Probes
You can view your map, or one of your @{"Probes" link "eng_equip"}. If you want to view a Probe you
must first type its number, from 0 to 99, on the black box next to the Probe
View button.
  In the View screen, there are four buttons. They are:
  - Scan. Do the actual viewing.
  - Exit. Return to your Base screen.
  - Upgrade. Probe upgrades cost 800 and map upgrades cost 1500. This will
enhance the intensity of your viewing.
  - Abort scan. If you are scanning, press this button to abort.

    - Switch to Excavator
Will transfer control to an Excavator, so you can actually play the game.

    - Save & Quit.
You can save your current game (not available in @{"unregistered" link "eng_money"} version) or quit
your game, returning to the main menu.

When you are in the Base, time is frozen, so you can take as many years as you
want to do all these actions.
@endnode
@node eng_play "What are you playing at?"

Actually playing the game is very simple. Use a joystick or the cursor keys to
control your Excavator.
  To use @{"Equipment" link "eng_equip"}, first choose a slot by pressing F1...F6. The Equipment
lights have four colours:
    - dark red = neither selected nor active.
    - bright red = selected, but not active.
    - dark green = not selected, but active.
    - bright green = both selected and active.
  (If you want an explanation of the Equipment, hold Shift while pressing
F1...F6.)
  To activate/deactivate your Equipment, press Fire/Spacebar. There are three
different Equipment types:
    - Togglers. These can either be switched on or off. These are the only ones
which can have green lights.
    - Activatives. Just select one and press Fire, and it will be carried out.
    - Background Equipment. Always active, no matter what you do.

To switch between Excavators, press F7...F10. To switch to the Base, press
Help.
  If you are standing adjacent to another Excavator, you can access the @{"Link" link "eng_link"}
screen by pressing Return. More of that later on.

The playing screen is of a darker grey colour than the Base screen, to show you
that time indeed passes in this screen, and is not frozen.
@endnode
@node eng_objects "I object!"

In the mines, you can meet the following types of scenery:

    - Earth. Comes in normal or yellow mineral shapes. Just walk on it, or dig
it. Dig it?
    - Rock. Can be walked on, but will headstrongly refuse to be destroyed in
any way.
    - Magma. Falling into magma will kill your Excavator. Cannot be destroyed.
    - Trees. Any artistic person knows that the two most beautiful things a
game can have are girls and trees. There are no girls in Excavation, so this
will have to do. Trees cannot be destroyed.
    - Ladders. Climb on them. Brown ladders are natural, white ladders are
artificial.
    - Blue arrows. These can be walked on, but only to the direction of the
arrows. Cannot be destroyed.
    - Teleports. If you touch a teleport, you will be randomly whisked some-
where else in the mines. Cannot be destroyed.
    - Jewels. There are Amethysts, Topazes and Sapphires. Just collect them.
    - Food. One apple will give you some extra units of food.

Jewels and Food may be found inside earth.

You can also meet the following creatures:

    - Ghosts. There are 12 Ghosts in total, and they wander aimlessly across
the mines. Maybe they are descendants of Inky, Pinky, Blinky and Clyde, maybe
not. Anyway, contact with them is fatal. They cannot be destroyed.
    - Amoeba. The Amoeba dwells deep underground and grows. Growing is its sole
meaning of life. It can be blown away, bit by bit, using the @{"Bombs" link "eng_equip"}. The Amoeba
doesn't kill either you or the Ghosts on contact.
@endnode
@node eng_equip "Welcome to the Excavation shop!"

There are 12 different pieces of Equipment available. Here they are:

    - SED (Standard Equipment Drill)
Will dig through normal earth, but not through mineral earth. Uses 1 unit of
power per dig. This is a Toggler.
    - HPD (High Performance Drill)
Will dig through both normal and mineral earth. Uses 1 unit of power per dig,
or 2 if digging through minerals. This is also a Toggler.
    - LCU (Ladder Creation Unit)
Creates ladders every time you go upwards. Ladders cost 3 units of power per
piece. A Toggler.
    - RLD (Radiophonic Location Device)
Will simply display your coordinates when active. Uses only 1 unit of power per
80 moves. Toggler.
    - VYB (Variable Yield Bombs)
Can be dropped on the ground, and then it will remain in place for five
seconds. After that, it will explode. It will destroy any destroyable things,
including your Excavators. The yield is simply the radius of the explosion.
This is an Activative. Uses some power.
    - ISP (Independent Surveillance Probes)
Can be sent away in a direction, travelling a certain distance or until it hits
something. After it has stopped, it can be viewed through the @{"Base" link "eng_base"} screen.
These can be destroyed with a bomb! An Activative, uses some power.
    - PSD (Power Supply Doubler)
Compresses the Excavator's power supply so that his usable supply is double the
size of his actual one. A Background Equipment.
    - PST (Power Supply Tripler)
Like the PSD, only triples. Also a Background Equipment.
    - HGL (Hidden Gem Locator)
When active, this will display any Jewels/Food hidden in the earth. Jewels are
displayed as white "pseudo-Jewels". Uses 1 unit of power per 20 moves. A
Toggler.
    - SDU (Self Destruction Unit)
When used, this will kill your Excavator. Uses no power. An Activative.
    - AFS (Auxiliary Food Supply)
Like the PSD, but compresses the Food supply. A Background Equipment.
    - FPU (Fusion Power Unit)
Will create its own power, completely freeing the Excavator from any needs of
power storage. Also a Background Equipment.
@endnode
