How to make really nice key strokes:
First, take a key. A simple door key will do, like the ones the nice mr.
Abloy makes. Then, get a brush. Weasel or camel hair works best, but if
you are an animal lover, you can use synthetic fur instead.
  Now kindly stroke the key with the brush. Begin with the outer edges,
making slow, careful strokes, and tickle the "teeth" of the key to keep
the key excited. Then go to the climax by stroking the inside of the
key's ring. Satisfaction guaranteed!

