@node HELP_ARROWS
@title "AmigaGuide® Help: Arrow Keys"
@{b}Up@{ub}
Fire an arrow up. This works best against flying creatures, like birds, but
if there is none present, you'd better take cover unless you want the
dropping arrow to pierce your head.

@{b}Down@{ub}
Fire an arrow down. This is only sensible if you are high up in a tower, or
aboard a flying vessel, for firing an arrow into the ground per se is
pointless.

@{b}Shift-Up@{ub}
Shift the arrow up, that is do not fire it, but move it yourself. You must
be on a ladder or know how to fly to do this.

@{b}Shift-Down@{ub}
Shift the arrow down, but what's the point? Gravity will get it there for
you.

@{b}Alt-Up@{ub}
Alt? What the heck does that mean?

@{b}Alt-Down@{ub}
Ditto.

@{b}Left@{ub}
Fire an arrow left. This direction, along with right, is the second best
recommended against groundbound creatures such as humans. The best direction
to fire an arrow in is, of course, forwards.

@{b}Right@{ub}
Just like left, only right.

@{b}Shift-Left@{ub}
Shift the arrow left. With this action, you can pretend the arrow is a sword
or a spear, and impale the enemy with it while the arrow is still in your
hand.

@{b}Shift-Right@{ub}
Just like shift left, only right.

